text: Natasha [ nuh-tah-shuh ] is a Russian female name. It is short for Natalia, which indicates "Natal Day". Natasha is a lovely name that boasts a range of interpretations. It can signify "born on Christmas day" or "birthday." This name is widely used for girls and is particularly prevalent in English- speaking nations. With a rich history, Natasha remains a favored choice for parents of baby girls, owing to its beauty and popularity. Celebrities and famous people include singer Natasha Bedingfield, Natasha Richardson and actress Natasha Lyonne.
